column12: VON IBDV (INFECTIOUS BURSAL DISEASE VIRUS) ABGELEITETE CHIMÄRE LEERE VIRUSÄHNLICHE PARTIKEL, VERFAHREN ZU DEREN HERSTELLUNG UND ANWENDUNGEN
column13: The chimeric empty viral-like particles derived from the infectious bursal disease virus (IBDV) are formed by the assembly of fusion proteins comprising a region A consisting of an IBDV pVP2 protein or a "1-n" fragment of said IBDV pVP2, wherein "n" is an integer comprised between 441 and 501, bound to a region B consisting of a heterologous polypeptide comprising a polypeptide of interest, such as a polypeptide useful for prophylactic, therapeutic or diagnostic purposes.

column12: PROCESS FOR OBTAINING POLY(ACRYLONITRILE-BUTADIENE-STYRENE) USING POLYBUTADIENE AS A PRECURSOR RUBBER WITH A HIGH CIS-1,4 CONTENT.
column13: The present invention describes a method for obtaining poly(acrylonitrile-styrene) (ABS) using polybutadiene (PB) as a precursor rubber with high-cis-1,4 content, using the in situ process in mass. Initially, the obtention of PB is performed by the selective polymerization of butadiene in the presence of styrene (St) as a solvent, by means of a catalytic system based on neodymium. Subsequently, the resulting solution of PB/St is added with different reagents established in an ABS recipe and are polymerized by free radicals, where the characteristics will depend on the macro and microstructure of the PB obtained in the first step.

column12: CONTINUOUS PROCESS FOR MANUFACTURING A SHEET AS A PREFORM FOR POLYETHYLENE FOAMS WITH NATURAL FIBER LOADING.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a continuous process for manufacturing a sheet that will be used as a preform to produce polyethylene foams loaded with agave fiber. This process consists of two stages: In the first stage, two concentrates are processed through an extrusion process, a concentrate comprising 46% by weight additives (azodicarbonamide, zinc oxide, peroxide and silicon dioxide), plus the ethylene-co-vinyl acetate (EVA) copolymer; the second concentrate is made up of agave fiber at 30% by weight and the ethylene-co-vinyl acetate copolymer. In the second stage, the sheet or preform is produced by the continuous extrusion process, using the concentrates of the first stage, which are diluted and mixed with the low density polyethylene polymers of and the ethylene-co-vinyl acetate copolymer. This way, agave fiber rectangular sheets or preforms are obtained at a concentration of 3 to 9% by weight. This preform can be cut in certain sizes or coiled to be foamed later; the st orage or shelf life of this preform can be of up to 9 months.
